### Description

Create a new job plan under a resource scope, based on an existing job template. 

### Request Parameters

#### Body Parameters

| Field           | Type   | Required | Description                                                                                                                                              |
|-----------------|--------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| bk_scope_type   | string | Yes      | Resource scope type. Allowed values: `biz` or `biz_set`                                                                                                  |
| bk_scope_id     | string | Yes      | Resource scope ID matching `bk_scope_type` (business id or business set id)                                                                              |
| job_template_id | long   | Yes      | Job template ID (must be > 0). Template must exist and the caller must hold both `view_job_template` and `create_job_plan` permissions on the scope.     |
| name            | string | Yes      | Plan name, 1–60 characters, must not contain HTML special characters `< > " '` (@NoXss), unique within (scope, template).                            |
| enable_steps    | array  | No       | List of template step ids to enable. If omitted, all template steps are enabled. An empty array is **not** allowed; ids outside the template will fail. |
| variables       | array  | No       | Optional overrides for template global variables, matched **by variable name**. Unknown names or mismatched value types will fail.                       |

##### variables

| Field           | Type    | Required | Description                                                                                                              |
|-----------------|---------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| name            | string  | Yes      | Template variable name (matched by name, **not** by id). Must be non-blank.                                              |
| value           | string  | No       | Variable value for string/namespace/ciphertext/array types. For **EXECUTE_OBJECT_LIST**, use `execute_target` instead of `value`. |
| execute_target  | object  | No       | Execute target override when the template variable type is EXECUTE_OBJECT_LIST and `follow_template=false`. Host dimensions only (see below). **`kube_container_filters` is not supported** on this API. |
| follow_template | boolean | No       | Whether to keep the template default. Defaults to `false`. When `true`, `value` is ignored and `execute_target` must not be provided. |

##### execute_target (EXECUTE_OBJECT_LIST only)

| Field                  | Type  | Required | Description                                                                                         |
|------------------------|-------|----------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| host_list              | array | No       | Static hosts: `bk_host_id`, or `bk_cloud_id` + `ip` (same as fast_execute_script).                  |
| dynamic_group_list     | array | No       | Dynamic group id list.                                                                              |
| topo_node_list         | array | No       | CMDB topo nodes with `id` and `node_type`.                                                          |
| kube_container_filters | array | No       | **Not supported** on this API; returns `ILLEGAL_PARAM_WITH_PARAM_NAME_AND_REASON` if provided.    |

At least one of `host_list`, `dynamic_group_list`, or `topo_node_list` must be non-empty. 

Fields other than those above (e.g. `description`, `type`, `required`, `changeable`) are determined by the template and **ignored** when supplied.

### Request Example

- POST

```json
{
    "bk_scope_type": "biz",
    "bk_scope_id": "2",
    "job_template_id": 1000,
    "name": "my-api-plan",
    "enable_steps": [101, 102, 103],
    "variables": [
        {
            "name": "TARGET_DIR",
            "value": "/data/release"
        },
        {
            "name": "KEEP_TEMPLATE_DEFAULT",
            "follow_template": true
        },
        {
            "name": "HOST_TARGET",
            "execute_target": {
                "host_list": [
                    {"bk_host_id": 10001}
                ],
                "dynamic_group_list": [
                    {"id": "dg-001"}
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

